description:
Add endpoint to list all ticks in a project.

## Endpoint

```
GET /api/projects/:project/ticks
```

## Response

```json
{
  "ticks": [
    {
      "id": "abc",
      "title": "Fix bug",
      "status": "open",
      "priority": 2,
      ...
    }
  ],
  "count": 42
}
```

## Query parameters (optional, future)

- `status` - filter by status (open, in_progress, closed, etc.)
- `type` - filter by type (task, bug, epic, etc.)
- `parent` - filter by parent tick ID

## Implementation in ProjectRoom.fetch()

```typescript
// GET /api/projects/:project/ticks
if (url.pathname.match(/\/ticks\/?$/) && request.method === "GET") {
  const ticksArray = Array.from(this.ticks.values());
  return Response.json({
    ticks: ticksArray,
    count: ticksArray.length,
  });
}
```

